cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of traversability estimation for mobile robots, which is a core problem in the field of robotics. The paper proposes a machine learning approach using convolutional neural networks to classify terrain patches as traversable or not. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as computer vision (cs.CV) since the approach involves processing heightmaps as images. The use of machine learning also suggests that the paper could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with terrain analysis and modeling, which could fall under computer graphics (cs.GR).
